        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 18 at 4:02PM EDT until July 18 at 4:45PM EDT by NWS Wakefield VA</headline>
        <description>SVRAKQ

The National Weather Service in Wakefield has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southeastern Louisa County in central Virginia...
Central Goochland County in central Virginia...
Northwestern Hanover County in central Virginia...

* Until 445 PM EDT.

* At 402 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 7 miles north of
Gum Spring, or 9 miles northeast of Hadensville, moving southeast
at 15 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to trees and powerlines.

* This severe thunderstorm will be near...
Montpelier around 425 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this severe thunderstorm include Orchid,
Oliver, Vontay, Coatesville, Johnsons Springs, Goodall, Mabelton,
Rockville, Dabneys, and Gilman.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Please report severe weather by calling 757-899-2415, posting to the
NWS Wakefield Facebook page, or using X @NWSWAKEFIELDVA.</instruction>
